<Author>jaxDC
<Content>Chic and Convenient We had a tough time settling on our hotels in Spain, and this was the last one we chose. It was a terrific selection and made our trip to Barcelona just that much better. First off, it's in a great location - off the main thoroughfares but exceptionally close to both the metro and the Aerobus stop (for a ridiculously easy trip to the airport on the morning we left). The lobby is just like the pictures - modern and sleek with couches and a piano. The man at the front desk most of the time we were there was a doll (!) and indulged all my questions and my rusty Spanish. The room was exactly as others have described. It's very clean and chic. It's true there's not a lot of privacy between the bathroom and the bedroom, but you can manage, and if you're a couple, it makes for a good laugh at times. We had a floor to ceiling window that opened up for fresh air and a view, but once it was closed, you couldn't hear a thing. The whole place was very quiet. We didn't eat at the hotel so I can't speak for the food, but the front desk was helpful with everything from restaurant recommendations to an adapter. This is just a terrific choice for a stay in Barcelona. Some of the other hotels we considered did look luxurious from the outside (montecarlo) and the lobby (1898), but I don't think you need to spend that kind of money to have a great time in Barcelona. The Petit Palace had plenty of character and sophistication and was much more affordable. 
