<Content>Good Location, shame about comfort When booking we went for location and this hotel didn't let us down. Near enough to get to most sights, including several very good cafes and restaurants, but out of the main busy streets, so night times were very quiet. The staff were very helpful, polite and spoke good English.The hotel is very modern with a stylish interior, but this can be its downside. When going for style, someone missed out, comfort, in the brief. Would have been good to have comfortable seating in bedrooms and reception. Also whoever designed the bathrooms, never checked out its practicality. In our room we had a bath with overhead shower. Admittedly a very good shower, but as the shower screen was fixed to the bath, it meant it was very difficult and dangerous getting in and out of the bath. I can see an accident waiting to happen! Ask for a bedroom with a separate shower cubicle.As this is supposed to be a High Tech Hotel, where was CD player?Overall I would recommend this hotel on location, but not to elderly people, people with back legs/ back or other minor disability, or someone looking for comfort. 
