<Author>alan_lusha
<Content>Amazing Hotel We stayed here for 3 nights as a treat for ourselves after missing out on a summer vacation; and any disappointment in missing out were instantly dispelled as the taxi pulled up outside the hotel and we saw what looked like the most stylish hotel we have ever stayed in.The reception area is very smart and modern with designer sofas, black marble, mood lighting and flat screen tv's, backed up by helpful and freindly staff.And when we entered our room, we was greeted by the same stylish design and quality, along with very celver mood lighting. The room was very modern and decorated with some real subtle flair.But our favourite was the bathroom which whilst it had a designer basin and toilet, the best was the huge shower cubicle (plenty big enough for two) and with the most fantastic shower, with body jets that could knock you out the bathroom when turned up to full power.This hotel is situated in a pefect place to see the city, sited just off the top of the Ramblers, just away from all the noise so nice and peaceful at night and is just around the corner from the Metro (Passige de Gracia) and Gaudis two buildings, Casa Batlo and Casa Mila.If you want to feel like you have stayed somewhere special and you fancy treating you partner to a bit of luxury (its worth it guys, trust me) and you want to be somewhere central for sight seeing, then I cannot recommend this hotel highly enough. 
