<Author>BURGEL
<Content>Good, will be better when copleted Stayed at this hotel between 22nd and 28th August, with my wife and two children.It had only been open a week and therefore all the facilities were not available however it was a very stylish hotel and I would recommend it.I went with my wife and two daughters (12  5) and stayed in one of the family rooms. The room itself was quite strange it had two areas one quite cramped with the a large double bed and two bunk beds, tv, wardrobes, mini fridge etc and the second had a sofabed, huge windows that were the whole length and height of the room but nothing else in it. It seemed a waste of the space, but I suppose it may be developed more in the future.There was a laptop with free internet access and each of the bunk beds had a small tv screen that could be pulled out of the wall, which the kids enjoyed despite only one english channel being available. MTV in German and Disney Channel in Spanish seemed to appeal to them.My only real complaints about the room would be the lack of wardrobe space, there was only enouggh room for 1 person's clothes and as you could potentially have 6 people staying there if the sofabed was used this was nowhere near enough. Also despite the shower being superb ( you can have the water coming out sideways if you want ) there is nowhere to put the soap and shampoo.The hotel is fairly central, it is only a five minute walk to a couple of different metro stations and also to Las Ramblas.Overall very stylish but not 100% practical, but I would go again. 
